<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<section xml:id="common-statements" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title> Other Policies</title>
  <subsection xml:id="group-work">
    <title>Group Work</title>
    <p>
        During class, we will often take time to work in groups. Just like in a professional environment, 
        you will be expected to work with others and communicate your ideas to them. I also encourage you to work in groups on your homework 
        and to discuss the problems with one another. Each individual should write up and turn in their own solutions.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="diversity-in-the-classroom">
    <title>Diversity and Inclusivity Statement</title>
    <p>
        I consider this classroom to be a place where you will be treated with respect, and I welcome individuals of all ages, backgrounds, 
        beliefs, ethnicities, genders, gender identities, gender expressions, national origins, religious affiliations, sexual orientations, 
        ability - and other visible and non-visible differences. All members of this class are expected to contribute to a respectful, 
        welcoming and inclusive environment for every other member of the class. 
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="academic-integrity">
    <title>Academic Integrity</title>
    <p>
        This course adheres to the <url href="https://www.capecod.edu/handbook/student-code-of-conduct/">CCCC Code of Conduct</url>.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="ai-policy">
    <title>AI Policy</title>
    <p>
        As an instructor, it is my job to evaluate <em>your</em> understanding of, and proficiency with, the material. Learning 
        how and why we do things a certain way, as well as obtaining a healthy amount of hands-on practice, 
        is integral to your learning in this course. So, for this course, it is never permissible to utilize generative AI to 
        create content which you intend to submit as your own work. Anything you submit must be a genuine reflection of your own understanding 
        of the material, submitted in good faith.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="technology">
    <title>Technology Use in the Classroom</title>
    <p>
        You are expected to keep your phone, laptop, tablet, headphones, and all other devices put away at all times during class. 
        During quizzes and exams, you must remove and stow any other smart devices (such as apple watches). Failure to remove such devices, or 
        otherwise accessing such devices, during assessments will result in an automatic zero. At the instructor's discretion, you 
        may be allowed to use a tablet for notes. This allowance can be revoked at any time, and will automatically be revoked if such a 
        device is used for anything other than taking notes.
    </p>
  </subsection>
  
</section>